Charl Schwartzel of South Africa plays his shot. AFP/Richard Heathcote/Getty Images JOHANNESBURG - South Africaâ€™s Charl Schwartzel took the lead ahead of compatriot Hennie du Plessis in the inaugural LIV Golf Invitational Series. The former Masters winner fired six birdies and an eagle, carding an opening five-under-par 65 to take a one-shot lead after the opening day. He is trailed by Du Plessis who is at 4 under while Branden Grace is in a tie for fifth on two under. Dustin Johnson and Phil Mickelson both share seventh place with England's Sam Horsfield and Laurie Canter after posting one-under-par 69s. Sergio Garcia finished one stroke over par in his first round.